# Coding Standards Rule

Delegates to the canonical AI context documents:

- [documentation/09-ai-context/coding-standards.md](../../documentation/09-ai-context/coding-standards.md) — Angular, NestJS, testing, accessibility
- [documentation/09-ai-context/naming-conventions.md](../../documentation/09-ai-context/naming-conventions.md) — files, symbols, API, DB IDs
- [documentation/09-ai-context/folder-structure.md](../../documentation/09-ai-context/folder-structure.md) — module layout
- [documentation/09-ai-context/technology-stack.md](../../documentation/09-ai-context/technology-stack.md) — pinned versions

When this rule applies, read and follow those documents in full before writing or modifying code.

**Screen-specific workflow:** For Angular screen generation from `05-ui-ux/` specs, also follow [.cursor/rules/generate-ui-screen.mdc](../rules/generate-ui-screen.mdc).

**Database entity docs:** Follow [documentation/04-database-design/database-design-standards.md](../../documentation/04-database-design/database-design-standards.md) via [@design-database-schema](../skills/design-database-schema/SKILL.md).

**Documentation generation:** Follow [.cursor/rules/generate-document.mdc](../rules/generate-document.mdc) and [documentation/09-ai-context/generation-rules.md](../../documentation/09-ai-context/generation-rules.md).
